### Terms and Conditions for SAINTCON

**Registration Terms and Conditions**

This registration agreement (the “Agreement”) is made between the UtahSAINT Organization (“UtahSAINT”) and the registrant. This Agreement includes and incorporates by reference the Privacy Policy/Terms of Use posted below.

#### 1. Cancellation Policy
- If you must cancel your registration, provide written notice to the UtahSAINT Organization.
   - **Refund Policy:**
     - Cancellation 28 or more days before the event: Full refund minus a transaction fee.
     - Cancellation 27 days or fewer before the event: No refunds.
     - Discount tickets are non-refundable and may not be transferred.
- Refunds will occur within thirty (30) days of receipt of the cancellation notice.
- You may transfer a paid ticket at any time at no cost. Failing to attend without cancellation or transfer means no refund will be issued.

#### 2. Transfer Policy
- Transfers of registrations are allowed with approval from the original registrant.
- Transfers must use the online “Registration Transfer Tool” and can only be transferred once.

#### 3. Visa Requirements
- You are responsible for your visa requirements.
- If your visa application is not granted, registration fees will be refunded per the refund policy.

#### 4. Age Requirements
- Attendees must be 18 years or older, or accompanied by a responsible adult.

#### 5. Discounts
- Only one (1) discount can be applied to each registration and cannot be combined.

#### 6. Photo ID
- A government-issued photo ID matching registration is required to collect the conference badge.

#### 7. Badge Control
- SAINTCON badges are the property of UtahSAINT and must be returned upon request. Badges must be visible during events.

#### 8. Photography, Audio, and Video Recording
- Recording of sessions is prohibited without consent.
- Photography requires consent of those being photographed.

#### 9. Information and Privacy Disclosure
- Registration information is confidential and not shared.

#### 10. Code of Conduct
- Attendees agree to follow the Code of Conduct. More details can be found at [SAINTCON Code of Conduct](https://www.saintcon.org/coc/).

#### 11. Force Majeure
- UtahSAINT is not liable for delays or cancellations caused by events beyond its control. Refund requests will be reviewed but are not guaranteed.

**Last Updated: Jan 29, 2023**